The President of the United States, Barack Obama, met with the Prince of Wales at the White House to discuss the strong alliance between the United States and the United Kingdom. The President expressed gratitude for the contributions of British forces in Afghanistan and Libya. They also discussed the Prince's work in environmental issues, such as halting deforestation and promoting sustainable food production. President Obama congratulated the Prince on the wedding of his son, Prince William, and extended his best wishes to the newlywed couple. The President mentioned his upcoming State visit to the United Kingdom at the invitation of Queen Elizabeth II.